#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:2
msgid "Compiling a Contract"
msgstr "編譯合約"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:5
msgid "Command-Line Compiler Tools"
msgstr "命令行編譯器工具"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:7
msgid ""
"Vyper includes the following command-line scripts for compiling contracts:"
msgstr "Vyper 包含以下用於編譯合約的命令行腳本："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:9
msgid "``vyper``: Compiles vyper contract or archive files"
msgstr "``vyper``：編譯 vyper 合約或封存檔案"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:10
msgid "``vyper-json``: Provides a JSON interface to the compiler"
msgstr "``vyper-json``：提供編譯器的 JSON 介面"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:14
msgid ""
"The ``--help`` flag gives verbose explanations of how to use each of these "
"scripts."
msgstr "``--help`` 旗標提供每個腳本使用方式的詳細說明。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:19
msgid "vyper"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:21
msgid ""
"``vyper`` provides CLI access to the compiler. It can generate various "
"outputs including simple binaries, ASTs, interfaces and source mappings."
msgstr ""
"``vyper`` 提供編譯器的命令行存取。它可以生成各種輸出，包括簡單的二進位檔、"
"AST、介面和來源碼映射。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:23
msgid "To compile a contract:"
msgstr "要編譯合約："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:25
msgid "$ vyper yourFileName.vy"
msgstr "$ vyper yourFileName.vy"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:30
msgid ""
"Include the ``-f`` flag to specify which output formats to return. Use "
"``vyper --help`` for a full list of output options."
msgstr ""
"使用 ``-f`` 旗標指定要傳回的輸出格式。使用 ``vyper --help`` 查看完整的輸出選"
"項列表。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:32
msgid ""
"$ vyper -f abi,abi_python,bytecode,bytecode_runtime,blueprint_bytecode,cfg,"
"cfg_runtime,interface,external_interface,ast,annotated_ast,integrity,ir,"
"ir_json,ir_runtime,asm,opcodes,opcodes_runtime,source_map,source_map_runtime,"
"archive,solc_json,method_identifiers,userdoc,devdoc,metadata,combined_json,"
"layout yourFileName.vy"
msgstr ""
"$ vyper -f abi,abi_python,bytecode,bytecode_runtime,blueprint_bytecode,cfg,"
"cfg_runtime,interface,external_interface,ast,annotated_ast,integrity,ir,"
"ir_json,ir_runtime,asm,opcodes,opcodes_runtime,source_map,source_map_runtime,"
"archive,solc_json,method_identifiers,userdoc,devdoc,metadata,combined_json,"
"layout yourFileName.vy"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:37
msgid ""
"The ``opcodes`` and ``opcodes_runtime`` output of the compiler has been "
"returning incorrect opcodes since ``0.2.0`` due to a lack of 0 padding "
"(patched via `PR 3735 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/pull/3735>`_). If "
"you rely on these functions for debugging, please use the latest patched "
"versions."
msgstr ""
"自 ``0.2.0`` 起，編譯器的 ``opcodes`` 和 ``opcodes_runtime`` 輸出由於缺少 0 "
"填充而一直傳回不正確的 opcode（已透過 `PR 3735 <https://github.com/vyperlang/"
"vyper/pull/3735>`_ 修補）。如果您依賴這些函數進行除錯，請使用最新的修補版本。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:39
msgid ""
"The ``-p`` flag allows you to set a root path that is used when searching "
"for interface files to import.  If none is given, it will default to the "
"current working directory. See :ref:`searching_for_imports` for more "
"information."
msgstr ""
"``-p`` 旗標允許您設定搜尋要匯入的介面檔案時使用的根路徑。如果未指定，則預設為"
"目前工作目錄。請參閱 :ref:`searching_for_imports` 以取得更多資訊。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:41
msgid "$ vyper -p yourProject yourProject/yourFileName.vy"
msgstr "$ vyper -p yourProject yourProject/yourFileName.vy"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:49
msgid "Storage Layout"
msgstr "儲存佈局"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:51
msgid "To display the default storage layout for a contract:"
msgstr "顯示合約的預設儲存佈局："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:53
msgid "$ vyper -f layout yourFileName.vy"
msgstr "$ vyper -f layout yourFileName.vy"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:57
msgid ""
"This outputs a JSON object detailing the locations for all state variables "
"as determined by the compiler."
msgstr "這會輸出一個 JSON 物件，詳細列出由編譯器決定的所有狀態變數位置。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:59
msgid "To override the default storage layout for a contract:"
msgstr "覆寫合約的預設儲存佈局："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:61
msgid "$ vyper --storage-layout-file storageLayout.json yourFileName.vy"
msgstr "$ vyper --storage-layout-file storageLayout.json yourFileName.vy"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:65
msgid ""
"The input to the ``--storage-layout-file`` flag must match the format of the "
"``.storage_layout`` field from the ``vyper -f layout`` command."
msgstr ""
"``--storage-layout-file`` 旗標的輸入格式必須與 ``vyper -f layout`` 命令的 ``."
"storage_layout`` 欄位格式相符。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:71
msgid "vyper-json"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:73
msgid ""
"``vyper-json`` provides a JSON interface for the compiler. It expects a :ref:"
"`JSON formatted input<vyper-json-input>` and returns the compilation result "
"in a :ref:`JSON formatted output<vyper-json-output>`."
msgstr ""
"``vyper-json`` 提供編譯器的 JSON 介面。它期望一個 :ref:`JSON 格式化的輸入"
"<vyper-json-input>`，並以 :ref:`JSON 格式化的輸出<vyper-json-output>` 傳回編"
"譯結果。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:75
msgid "To compile from JSON supplied via ``stdin``:"
msgstr "從透過 ``stdin`` 提供的 JSON 進行編譯："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:77
msgid "$ vyper-json"
msgstr "$ vyper-json"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:81
msgid "To compile from a JSON file:"
msgstr "從 JSON 檔案進行編譯："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:83
msgid "$ vyper-json yourProject.json"
msgstr "$ vyper-json yourProject.json"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:87
msgid ""
"By default, the output is sent to ``stdout``. To redirect to a file, use the "
"``-o`` flag:"
msgstr ""
"預設情況下，輸出會傳送到 ``stdout``。要重定向到檔案，請使用 ``-o`` 旗標："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:89
msgid "$ vyper-json -o compiled.json"
msgstr "$ vyper-json -o compiled.json"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:94
msgid "Importing Interfaces"
msgstr "匯入介面"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:96
msgid ""
"``vyper-json`` searches for imported interfaces in the following sequence:"
msgstr "``vyper-json`` 按以下順序搜尋匯入的介面："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:98
msgid "Interfaces defined in the ``interfaces`` field of the input JSON."
msgstr "在輸入 JSON 的 ``interfaces`` 欄位中定義的介面。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:99
msgid ""
"Derived interfaces generated from contracts in the ``sources`` field of the "
"input JSON."
msgstr "從輸入 JSON 的 ``sources`` 欄位中的合約所生成的衍生介面。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:101
msgid ""
"See :ref:`searching_for_imports` for more information on Vyper's import "
"system."
msgstr "請參閱 :ref:`searching_for_imports` 以取得 Vyper 匯入系統的更多資訊。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:104
msgid "Online Compilers"
msgstr "在線編譯器"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:107
msgid "Try VyperLang!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:109
msgid ""
"`Try VyperLang! <https://try.vyperlang.org>`_ is a JupyterHub instance "
"hosted by the Vyper team as a sandbox for developing and testing contracts "
"in Vyper. It requires github for login, and supports deployment via the "
"browser."
msgstr ""
"`Try VyperLang! <https://try.vyperlang.org>`_ 是由 Vyper 團隊託管的 "
"JupyterHub 實例，作為使用 Vyper 開發和測試合約的沙盒環境。它需要 GitHub 進行"
"登入，並支援透過瀏覽器進行部署。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:112
msgid "Remix IDE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:114
msgid ""
"`Remix IDE <https://remix.ethereum.org>`_ is a compiler and JavaScript VM "
"for developing and testing contracts in Vyper, as well as Solidity."
msgstr ""
"`Remix IDE <https://remix.ethereum.org>`_ 是一個編譯器和 JavaScript VM，用於"
"以 Vyper 以及 Solidity 開發和測試合約。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:118
msgid ""
"While the Vyper version of the Remix IDE compiler is updated on a regular "
"basis, it might be a bit behind the latest version found in the master "
"branch of the repository. Make sure the byte code matches the output from "
"your local compiler."
msgstr ""
"雖然 Remix IDE 的 Vyper 版本編譯器會定期更新，但可能比儲存庫 master 分支中的"
"最新版本稍落後。請確保位元組碼與您本機編譯器的輸出相符。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:123
msgid "Compiler Optimization Modes"
msgstr "編譯器最佳化模式"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:125
msgid ""
"The Vyper CLI tool accepts an optimization mode ``\"none\"``, "
"``\"codesize\"``, or ``\"gas\"`` (default). It can be set using the ``--"
"optimize`` flag. For example, invoking ``vyper --optimize codesize "
"MyContract.vy`` will compile the contract, optimizing for code size. As a "
"rough summary of the differences between gas and codesize mode, in gas "
"optimized mode, the compiler will try to generate bytecode which minimizes "
"gas (up to a point), including:"
msgstr ""
"Vyper CLI 工具接受 ``\"none\"``、``\"codesize\"`` 或 ``\"gas\"``（預設）最佳"
"化模式。可以使用 ``--optimize`` 旗標進行設定。例如，呼叫 ``vyper --optimize "
"codesize MyContract.vy`` 將編譯合約並針對程式碼大小進行最佳化。粗略總結 gas "
"和 codesize 模式之間的差異，在 gas 最佳化模式下，編譯器會嘗試生成最小化 gas "
"使用的位元組碼（在某種程度上），包括："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:127
msgid "using a sparse selector table which optimizes for gas over codesize"
msgstr "使用稀疏選擇器表，相對於程式碼大小更優化 gas"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:128
msgid "inlining some constants, and"
msgstr "內聯一些常數，以及"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:129
msgid "trying to unroll some loops, especially for data copies."
msgstr "嘗試展開一些迴圈，尤其是針對資料複製。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:131
msgid ""
"In codesize optimized mode, the compiler will try hard to minimize codesize "
"by"
msgstr "在 codesize 最佳化模式下，編譯器會努力透過以下方式最小化程式碼大小"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:133
msgid "using a dense selector table"
msgstr "使用密集選擇器表"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:134
msgid "out-lining code, and"
msgstr "將程式碼外聯（out-lining），以及"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:135
msgid "using more loops for data copies."
msgstr "對資料複製使用更多迴圈。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:138
msgid "Enabling Experimental Code Generation"
msgstr "啟用實驗性程式碼生成"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:140
msgid ""
"When compiling, you can use the CLI flag ``--experimental-codegen`` (or its "
"alias ``--venom-experimental``) to activate the new `Venom IR <https://"
"github.com/vyperlang/vyper/blob/master/vyper/venom/README.md>`_. Venom IR is "
"inspired by LLVM IR and enables new advanced analysis and optimizations."
msgstr ""
"編譯時，您可以使用 CLI 旗標 ``--experimental-codegen``（或其別名 ``--venom-"
"experimental``）來啟用新的 `Venom IR <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/"
"blob/master/vyper/venom/README.md>`_。Venom IR 受 LLVM IR 啟發，並支援新的進"
"階分析和最佳化。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:146
msgid "Setting the Target EVM Version"
msgstr "設定目標 EVM 版本"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:148
msgid ""
"When you compile your contract code, you can specify the target Ethereum "
"Virtual Machine version to compile for, to access or avoid particular "
"features. You can specify the version either with a source code pragma or as "
"a compiler option. It is recommended to use the compiler option when you "
"want flexibility (for instance, ease of deploying across different chains), "
"and the source code pragma when you want bytecode reproducibility (for "
"instance, when verifying code on a block explorer)."
msgstr ""
"編譯合約程式碼時，您可以指定要編譯的目標以太坊虛擬機版本，以存取或避免特定功"
"能。您可以透過來源碼 pragma 或編譯器選項來指定版本。當您需要靈活性時（例如，"
"方便在不同鏈上部署），建議使用編譯器選項；當您需要位元組碼可重現性時（例如，"
"在區塊瀏覽器上驗證程式碼），則建議使用來源碼 pragma。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:151
msgid ""
"If the evm version specified by the compiler options conflicts with the "
"source code pragma, an exception will be raised and compilation will not "
"continue."
msgstr ""
"如果編譯器選項指定的 EVM 版本與來源碼 pragma 衝突，將會引發例外且編譯不會繼"
"續。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:153
msgid ""
"For instance, the adding the following pragma to a contract indicates that "
"it should be compiled for the \"prague\" fork of the EVM."
msgstr ""
"例如，將以下 pragma 新增到合約中表示應針對 EVM 的「prague」分叉進行編譯。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:155
msgid "#pragma evm-version prague"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:161
msgid ""
"Compiling for the wrong EVM version can result in wrong, strange, or failing "
"behavior. Please ensure, especially if running a private chain, that you use "
"matching EVM versions."
msgstr ""
"針對錯誤的 EVM 版本進行編譯可能導致錯誤、異常或失敗的行為。請確保使用相符的 "
"EVM 版本，尤其是在執行私有鏈時。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:163
msgid ""
"When compiling via the ``vyper`` CLI, you can specify the EVM version option "
"using the ``--evm-version`` flag:"
msgstr ""
"透過 ``vyper`` CLI 編譯時，您可以使用 ``--evm-version`` 旗標指定 EVM 版本選"
"項："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:165
msgid "$ vyper --evm-version [VERSION]"
msgstr "$ vyper --evm-version [VERSION]"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:169
msgid ""
"When using the JSON interface, you can include the ``\"evmVersion\"`` key "
"within the ``\"settings\"`` field:"
msgstr ""
"使用 JSON 介面時，您可以在 ``\"settings\"`` 欄位中包含 ``\"evmVersion\"`` "
"鍵："

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:171
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"settings\": {\n"
"        \"evmVersion\": \"[VERSION]\"\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"{\n"
"    \"settings\": {\n"
"        \"evmVersion\": \"[VERSION]\"\n"
"    }\n"
"}"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:180
msgid "Target Options"
msgstr "目標選項"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:182
msgid ""
"The following is a list of supported EVM versions, and changes in the "
"compiler introduced with each version. Backward compatibility is not "
"guaranteed between each version. In general, the compiler team maintains an "
"informal policy that the compiler will support 3 years of hard fork "
"rulesets, but this policy may be revisited as appropriate."
msgstr ""
"以下是支援的 EVM 版本列表，以及每個版本引入的編譯器變更。各版本之間不保證向後"
"相容性。一般來說，編譯器團隊維持非正式政策，即編譯器將支援 3 年的硬分叉規則"
"集，但此政策可能會根據情況重新檢視。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:189
msgid ""
"``block.difficulty`` is deprecated in favor of its new alias, ``block."
"prevrandao``."
msgstr "``block.difficulty`` 已被棄用，改為使用其新別名 ``block.prevrandao``。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:193
msgid ""
"The ``PUSH0`` opcode is automatically generated by the compiler instead of "
"``PUSH1 0``"
msgstr "``PUSH0`` opcode 由編譯器自動生成，取代 ``PUSH1 0``"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:197
msgid ""
"The ``transient`` keyword allows declaration of variables which live in "
"transient storage"
msgstr "``transient`` 關鍵字允許宣告存在於暫態儲存中的變數"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:198
msgid ""
"Functions marked with ``@nonreentrant`` are protected with TLOAD/TSTORE "
"instead of SLOAD/SSTORE"
msgstr ""
"標記為 ``@nonreentrant`` 的函數使用 TLOAD/TSTORE 而非 SLOAD/SSTORE 進行保護"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:199
msgid ""
"The ``MCOPY`` opcode will be generated automatically by the compiler for "
"most memory operations."
msgstr "對於大多數記憶體操作，編譯器將自動生成 ``MCOPY`` opcode。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:206
msgid "Controlling Warnings"
msgstr "控制警告"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:208
msgid ""
"Vyper allows suppression of warnings via the CLI flag ``-Wnone``, or "
"promotion of (all) warnings to errors via the ``-Werror`` flag."
msgstr ""
"Vyper 允許透過 CLI 旗標 ``-Wnone`` 來抑制警告，或透過 ``-Werror`` 旗標將（所"
"有）警告升級為錯誤。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:210
msgid "$ vyper -Wnone foo.vy   # suppress warnings"
msgstr "$ vyper -Wnone foo.vy   # 抑制警告"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:214
msgid "$ vyper -Werror foo.vy   # promote warnings to errors"
msgstr "$ vyper -Werror foo.vy   # 將警告升級成錯誤"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:222
msgid "Integrity Hash"
msgstr "完整性雜湊"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:224
msgid ""
"To help tooling detect whether two builds are the same, Vyper provides the "
"``-f integrity`` output, which outputs the integrity hash of a contract. The "
"integrity hash is recursively defined as the sha256 of the source code with "
"the integrity hashes of its dependencies (imports) and storage layout "
"overrides (if provided)."
msgstr ""
"為了幫助工具檢測兩個建置是否相同，Vyper 提供了 ``-f integrity`` 輸出，它會輸"
"出合約的完整性雜湊。完整性雜湊遞迴定義為來源碼的 sha256 加上其依賴項（匯入）"
"的完整性雜湊和儲存配置覆蓋（如果有提供的話）。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:229
msgid "Vyper Archives"
msgstr "Vyper 封存檔"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:231
msgid ""
"A Vyper archive is a compileable bundle of input sources and settings. "
"Technically, it is a `ZIP file <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"ZIP_(file_format)>`_, with a special structure to make it useable as input "
"to the compiler. It can use any suffix, but the convention is to use a ``."
"zip`` suffix or ``.vyz`` suffix. It must contain a ``MANIFEST/`` folder, "
"with the following directory structure."
msgstr ""
"Vyper 封存檔是一個可編譯的輸入來源碼和設定組合。技術上來說，它是一個 `ZIP 檔"
"案 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ZIP_(file_format)>`_，具有特殊結構使其可作"
"為編譯器的輸入。它可以使用任何副檔名，但慣例是使用 ``.zip`` 或 ``.vyz`` 副檔"
"名。它必須包含一個 ``MANIFEST/`` 資料夾，具有以下目錄結構。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:235
msgid ""
"MANIFEST\n"
"├── cli_settings.txt\n"
"├── compilation_targets\n"
"├── compiler_version\n"
"├── integrity\n"
"├── settings.json\n"
"├── searchpaths\n"
"└── storage_layout.json [OPTIONAL]"
msgstr ""
"MANIFEST\n"
"├── cli_settings.txt\n"
"├── compilation_targets\n"
"├── compiler_version\n"
"├── integrity\n"
"├── settings.json\n"
"├── searchpaths\n"
"└── storage_layout.json [OPTIONAL]"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:244
msgid ""
"``cli_settings.txt`` is a text representation of the settings that were used "
"on the compilation run that generated this archive."
msgstr "``cli_settings.txt`` 是生成此封存檔的編譯執行中所使用設定的文字表示。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:245
msgid ""
"``compilation_targets`` is a newline separated list of compilation targets. "
"Currently only one compilation is supported"
msgstr "``compilation_targets`` 是以換行分隔的編譯目標列表。目前僅支援一個編譯"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:246
msgid ""
"``compiler_version`` is a text representation of the compiler version used "
"to generate this archive"
msgstr "``compiler_version`` 是用於生成此封存檔的編譯器版本的文字表示"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:247
msgid ""
"``integrity`` is the :ref:`integrity hash <integrity-hash>` of the input "
"contract"
msgstr "``integrity`` 是輸入合約的 :ref:`完整性雜湊 <integrity-hash>`"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:248
msgid ""
"``searchpaths`` is a newline-separated list of the search paths used on this "
"compilation run"
msgstr "``searchpaths`` 是以換行分隔的此次編譯執行中使用的搜尋路徑列表"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:249
msgid ""
"``settings.json`` is a json representation of the settings used on this "
"compilation run. It is 1:1 with ``cli_settings.txt``, but both are provided "
"as they are convenient for different workflows (typically, manually vs "
"automated)."
msgstr ""
"``settings.json`` 是此次編譯執行中使用的設定的 JSON 表示。它與 "
"``cli_settings.txt`` 是 1:1 對應的，但兩者都提供，因為它們對不同的工作流程"
"（通常分別用於手動和自動化）都很方便。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:250
msgid ""
"``storage_layout.json`` is a json representation of the storage layout "
"overrides to be used on this compilation run. It is optional."
msgstr ""
"``storage_layout.json`` 是要在此次編譯執行中使用的儲存佈局覆寫的 JSON 表示。"
"此為選用項目。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:252
msgid ""
"A Vyper archive file can be produced by requesting the ``-f archive`` output "
"format. The compiler can also produce the archive in base64 encoded form "
"using the ``--base64`` flag. The Vyper compiler can accept both ``.vyz`` and "
"base64-encoded Vyper archives directly as input."
msgstr ""
"Vyper 封存檔案可以透過請求 ``-f archive`` 輸出格式來產生。編譯器也可以使用 "
"``--base64`` 旗標以 base64 編碼形式產生封存檔。Vyper 編譯器可以直接接受 ``."
"vyz`` 和 base64 編碼的 Vyper 封存檔作為輸入。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:254
msgid ""
"$ vyper -f archive my_contract.vy -o my_contract.vyz  # write the archive to "
"my_contract.vyz\n"
"$ vyper -f archive my_contract.vy --base64 > my_contract.vyz.b64  # write "
"the archive, as base64-encoded text\n"
"$ vyper my_contract.vyz  # compile my_contract.vyz\n"
"$ vyper my_contract.vyz.b64  # compile my_contract.vyz.b64"
msgstr ""
"$ vyper -f archive my_contract.vy -o my_contract.vyz  # 將封存檔寫入 "
"my_contract.vyz\n"
"$ vyper -f archive my_contract.vy --base64 > my_contract.vyz.b64  # 將封存檔"
"寫入為 base64 編碼文字\n"
"$ vyper my_contract.vyz  # 編譯 my_contract.vyz\n"
"$ vyper my_contract.vyz.b64  # 編譯 my_contract.vyz.b64"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:262
msgid "Compiler Input and Output JSON Description"
msgstr "編譯器輸入與輸出 JSON 說明"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:264
msgid ""
"JSON input/output is provided for compatibility with solidity, however, the "
"recommended way is to use the aforementioned :ref:`Vyper archives <vyper-"
"archives>`. So-called \"standard json\" input can be generated from a "
"contract using the ``vyper -f solc_json`` output format."
msgstr ""
"提供 JSON 輸入/輸出是為了與 Solidity 相容，然而建議的方式是使用前述的 :ref:"
"`Vyper 封存檔 <vyper-archives>`。所謂的「標準 json」輸入可以使用 ``vyper -f "
"solc_json`` 輸出格式從合約生成。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:266
msgid ""
"Where possible, the Vyper JSON compiler formats follow those of `Solidity "
"<https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/using-the-compiler.html#compiler-"
"input-and-output-json-description>`_."
msgstr ""
"在可能的情況下，Vyper JSON 編譯器格式遵循 `Solidity <https://solidity."
"readthedocs.io/en/latest/using-the-compiler.html#compiler-input-and-output-"
"json-description>`_ 的格式。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:271
msgid "Input JSON Description"
msgstr "輸入 JSON 說明"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:273
msgid ""
"The following example describes the expected input format of ``vyper-json``. "
"(Comments are not normally permitted in JSON and are used here for "
"explanatory purposes)."
msgstr ""
"以下範例描述了 ``vyper-json`` 的預期輸入格式。（註解通常不允許在 JSON 中使"
"用，此處僅用於說明目的）。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:275
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    // Required: Source code language. Must be set to \"Vyper\".\n"
"    \"language\": \"Vyper\",\n"
"    // Required\n"
"    // Source codes given here will be compiled.\n"
"    \"sources\": {\n"
"        \"contracts/foo.vy\": {\n"
"            // Optional: keccak256 hash of the source file\n"
"            \"keccak256\": \"0x234...\",\n"
"            // Required: literal contents of the source file\n"
"            \"content\": \"@external\\ndef foo() -> bool:\\n    return "
"True\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    // Optional\n"
"    // Sources given here are made available for import by the contracts\n"
"    // that are compiled. If the suffix is \".vy\", the compiler will "
"expect\n"
"    // Vyper syntax. If the suffix is \"abi\" the compiler will expect an\n"
"    // ABI object.\n"
"    \"interfaces\": {\n"
"        \"contracts/bar.vy\": {\n"
"            \"content\": \"\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"contracts/baz.json\": {\n"
"            \"abi\": []\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    // Optional\n"
"    // Storage layout overrides for the contracts that are compiled\n"
"    \"storage_layout_overrides\": {\n"
"        \"contracts/foo.vy\": {\n"
"            \"a\": {\"type\": \"uint256\", \"slot\": 1, \"n_slots\": 1},\n"
"            \"b\": {\"type\": \"uint256\", \"slot\": 0, \"n_slots\": 1},\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    // Required\n"
"    \"settings\": {\n"
"        \"evmVersion\": \"prague\",  // EVM version to compile for. Can be "
"london, paris, shanghai, cancun or prague (default).\n"
"        // optional, optimization mode\n"
"        // defaults to \"gas\". can be one of \"gas\", \"codesize\", "
"\"none\",\n"
"        // false  and true (the last two are for backwards compatibility).\n"
"        \"optimize\": \"gas\",\n"
"        // optional, whether or not the bytecode should include Vyper's "
"signature\n"
"        // defaults to true\n"
"        \"bytecodeMetadata\": true,\n"
"        // optional, whether to use the experimental venom pipeline\n"
"        // defaults to false\n"
"        \"experimentalCodegen\": false,\n"
"        // the search paths to use for resolving imports\n"
"        \"search_paths\": [],\n"
"        // The following is used to select desired outputs based on file "
"names.\n"
"        // File names are given as keys, a star as a file name matches all "
"files.\n"
"        // Outputs can also follow the Solidity format where second level "
"keys\n"
"        // denoting contract names - all 2nd level outputs are applied to "
"the file.\n"
"        //\n"
"        // To select all possible compiler outputs: \"outputSelection: "
"{ '*': [\"*\"] }\"\n"
"        // Note that this might slow down the compilation process "
"needlessly.\n"
"        //\n"
"        // The available output types are as follows:\n"
"        //\n"
"        //    abi - The contract ABI\n"
"        //    ast - Abstract syntax tree\n"
"        //    interface - Derived interface of the contract, in proper Vyper "
"syntax\n"
"        //    ir - intermediate representation of the code\n"
"        //    userdoc - Natspec user documentation\n"
"        //    devdoc - Natspec developer documentation\n"
"        //    evm.bytecode.object - Bytecode object\n"
"        //    evm.bytecode.opcodes - Opcodes list\n"
"        //    evm.bytecode.sourceMap - Source mapping (useful for "
"debugging)\n"
"        //    evm.deployedBytecode.object - Deployed bytecode object\n"
"        //    evm.deployedBytecode.opcodes - Deployed opcodes list\n"
"        //    evm.deployedBytecode.sourceMap - Deployed source mapping "
"(useful for debugging)\n"
"        //    evm.methodIdentifiers - The list of function hashes\n"
"        //    layout - Storage layout of the contract\n"
"        //\n"
"        // Using `evm`, `evm.bytecode`, etc. will select every target part "
"of that output.\n"
"        // Additionally, `*` can be used as a wildcard to request "
"everything.\n"
"        // Note that the sourceMapFull.pc_ast_map is the recommended source "
"map to use;\n"
"        // the other types are included for legacy and compatibility "
"reasons.\n"
"        //\n"
"        \"outputSelection\": {\n"
"            \"*\": [\"evm.bytecode\", \"abi\"],  // Enable the abi and "
"bytecode outputs for every single contract\n"
"            \"contracts/foo.vy\": [\"ast\"]  // Enable the ast output for "
"contracts/foo.vy\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:366
msgid "Output JSON Description"
msgstr "輸出 JSON 說明"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:368
msgid ""
"The following example describes the output format of ``vyper-json``. "
"Comments are of course not permitted and used here *only for explanatory "
"purposes*."
msgstr ""
"以下範例描述了 ``vyper-json`` 的輸出格式。註解當然不允許使用，此處僅用於說明"
"目的。"

#: ../../../compiling-a-contract.rst:370
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    // The compiler version used to generate the JSON\n"
"    \"compiler\": \"vyper-0.4.0\",\n"
"    // Optional: not present if no errors/warnings were encountered\n"
"    \"errors\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"        // Optional: Location within the source file.\n"
"        \"sourceLocation\": {\n"
"            \"file\": \"source_file.vy\",\n"
"            \"lineno\": 5,\n"
"            \"col_offset\": 11\n"
"        },\n"
"        // Mandatory: Exception type, such as \"JSONError\", "
"\"StructureException\", etc.\n"
"        \"type\": \"TypeMismatch\",\n"
"        // Mandatory: Component where the error originated, such as "
"\"json\", \"compiler\", \"vyper\", etc.\n"
"        \"component\": \"compiler\",\n"
"        // Mandatory (\"error\" or \"warning\")\n"
"        \"severity\": \"error\",\n"
"        // Mandatory\n"
"        \"message\": \"Unsupported type conversion: int128 to bool\"\n"
"        // Optional: the message formatted with source location\n"
"        \"formattedMessage\": \"line 5:11 Unsupported type conversion: "
"int128 to bool\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    ],\n"
"    // Optional: not present if there are no storage layout overrides\n"
"    \"storage_layout_overrides\": {\n"
"        \"contracts/foo.vy\": {\n"
"            \"a\": {\"type\": \"uint256\", \"slot\": 1, \"n_slots\": 1},\n"
"            \"b\": {\"type\": \"uint256\", \"slot\": 0, \"n_slots\": 1},\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    // This contains the file-level outputs. Can be limited/filtered by the "
"outputSelection settings.\n"
"    \"sources\": {\n"
"        \"source_file.vy\": {\n"
"            // Identifier of the source (used in source maps)\n"
"            \"id\": 0,\n"
"            // The AST object\n"
"            \"ast\": {},\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    // This contains the contract-level outputs. Can be limited/filtered by "
"the outputSelection settings.\n"
"    \"contracts\": {\n"
"        \"source_file.vy\": {\n"
"            // The contract name will always be the file name without a "
"suffix\n"
"            \"source_file\": {\n"
"                // The Ethereum Contract ABI.\n"
"                // See https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/abi-spec."
"html\n"
"                \"abi\": [],\n"
"                // Natspec developer documentation\n"
"                \"devdoc\": {},\n"
"                // Intermediate representation (the IR node tree as a JSON "
"object)\n"
"                \"ir\": {},\n"
"                // Natspec user documentation\n"
"                \"userdoc\": {},\n"
"                // Storage layout of the contract\n"
"                \"layout\": {\n"
"                    \"storage_layout\": {\n"
"                        \"variableName\": {\n"
"                            \"type\": \"uint256\",\n"
"                            \"slot\": 0,\n"
"                            \"n_slots\": 1\n"
"                        }\n"
"                    }\n"
"                },\n"
"                // EVM-related outputs\n"
"                \"evm\": {\n"
"                    \"bytecode\": {\n"
"                        // The bytecode as a hex string.\n"
"                        \"object\": \"00fe\",\n"
"                        // Opcodes list (string)\n"
"                        \"opcodes\": \"\",\n"
"                        // The creation source mapping.\n"
"                        \"sourceMap\": {\n"
"                            \"breakpoints\": [],\n"
"                            \"error_map\": {},\n"
"                            \"pc_ast_map\": {},\n"
"                            \"pc_ast_map_item_keys\": [],\n"
"                            \"pc_breakpoints\": [],\n"
"                            \"pc_jump_map\": {},\n"
"                            \"pc_pos_map\": {},\n"
"                            // The creation source mapping as a string.\n"
"                            \"pc_pos_map_compressed\": \"\"\n"
"                        }\n"
"                    },\n"
"                    \"deployedBytecode\": {\n"
"                        // The deployed bytecode as a hex string.\n"
"                        \"object\": \"00fe\",\n"
"                        // Deployed opcodes list (string)\n"
"                        \"opcodes\": \"\",\n"
"                        // The deployed source mapping.\n"
"                        \"sourceMap\": {\n"
"                            \"breakpoints\": [],\n"
"                            \"error_map\": {},\n"
"                            \"pc_ast_map\": {},\n"
"                            \"pc_ast_map_item_keys\": [],\n"
"                            \"pc_breakpoints\": [],\n"
"                            \"pc_jump_map\": {},\n"
"                            \"pc_pos_map\": {},\n"
"                            // The deployed source mapping as a string.\n"
"                            \"pc_pos_map_compressed\": \"\"\n"
"                        }\n"
